Ticket Lao +856 (0)20 5255 8787
Other agents may be available.
If your return journey to the UK transits another country, you should check whether it is subject to a travel ban or any other additional requirements, before committing to flights. Restrictions are liable to change and therefore you should stay up to date with our travel advice for countries that you will be transiting.
Lao Government COVID-19 regulations require that you inform the Embassy if youâ€™re departing Laos.
If you are leaving Laos, email BritishEmbassy.Vientiane@fcdo.gov.uk with your full name, contact telephone number, passport number, flight details or border crossing point and a scan or photograph of the identification page of your passport. Please contact the Embassy at least 7 working days before your departure and clearly state where in Laos you are traveling from.
The Embassy will inform the Lao Ministry of Foreign Affairs of departing British Nationals, as required by the Lao Government.
Departing after 12 December 2021
If you plan to fly from, or depart, Laos after 12 December 2021, you do not need to notify the British Embassy. We have confirmed to the Ministry of Foreign Affairs that the final notification we will send will be for any flights on 12 December. Normal immigration procedures should be now in operation.
The British Embassy recommends arriving to check in as early as possible for flights, and building in additional time for border crossings to take into account any teething issues as immigration processes restart.
Any British nationals who have contacted us regarding departures after this date should receive a communication about the new arrangements.
Further information
The British Embassy Vientiane will also issue urgent updates on the UKinLaos Facebook page.
